## ⚙️ Configuration Details

The `config.yml` file allows you to customize rank thresholds, sounds, and messages.

### 🎖️ Rank System (Grading)
Compares the player's time against the **Top 1 of the Parkour (World Record)**.
```yaml
rank-system:
  enabled: true
  thresholds: # MS difference against the Top 1
    S: 5000     # Top 1 + 5.0 seconds
    A: 15000    # Top 1 + 15.0 seconds
    B: 30000    # Top 1 + 30.0 seconds
    C: 60000    # Top 1 + 60.0 seconds
```
> **Note:** If a player achieves the absolute record (Historical Best Time), they will always be awarded the **SS** rank.

### 🎁 Reward System
Rewards are managed by navigating to `/pka` -> **Right Click** on a parkour -> **Rewards**. They support 3 different prefixes:

| Prefix      | Behavior (Examples) |
| :---        |    :----   |
| `[console]` | The default prefix. Silently executes a command from the console. <br>Ex: `[console] eco give {player} 500`|
| `[player]`  | Forces the winning player to execute a command as themselves.<br>Ex: `[player] me is a parkour legend.` |
| `[message]` | Sends a private text/message using MiniMessage directly.<br>Ex: `[message] <green>You won 5 exclusive keys!` |

*(Available variables: `{player}`, plus native support for all `PlaceholderAPI` tags)*

