## 💡 Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

**Q: Why don't I receive rewards when I finish the parkour while testing the plugin?**
**A:** By design, rewards are only given the **first time** you beat your own `Personal Best`. Once you finish, your time is saved in the database. To test rewards again, open `/pka edit`, right-click the parkour, click the TNT block (Reset Leaderboard) to wipe your record, and run the parkour again.

**Q: How do I modify the inventory given to a player while jumping?**
**A:** Go to `config.yml` -> `session-items` section. There you can define the *Slot* and *Material* for the Quick Restart (Back to start), Checkpoint, and Quit items.

**Q: If I fall off the map into the void, it takes too long to restart. How do I prevent this?**
**A:** The plugin features smart void teleportation. In `config.yml` under `void.extra-buffer`, you can adjust how quickly it detects a player falling below the world border (min-height) to seamlessly return them to their last checkpoint before they take physical damage.
